    <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545"> 
      <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head> 
      <p>Senior Extension Associate in the Family Life Development Center,
        Cornell University.</p> 
    </bioghist> 
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520"> 
      <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head> 
      <p>Curriculum and conference material, correspondence, reports, project
        proposals, films, and publications concerning work done in the Family Life
        Development Center (FLDC) concerning child abuse and neglect, specifically ACT
        (Assets Coming Together) for Youth, a project of the New York State Dept. of
        Health; the Community Lifelines Program; Statewide Teamwork for Abused Runaways
        (STAR); and reports written by Barry for the United States Advisory Board on
        Child Abuse and Neglect. Includes two films, "Child Abuse: A Total Treatment
        Perspective" and "Child Abuse: Perspective on Being a Parent".</p> 
    </scopecontent> 
